[{"question":"And if you were advising Charlie Sheen now, what would you do to try and perhaps rebuild the bridge that\u0027s crashed around him?","answer":"You know, Stan\u0027s a very good friend, and he did the right thing.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":42,"aSentId":43},{"question":"He\u0027s almost playing the Hollywood power game in his own way, and doing it in a way no one\u0027s done before, isn\u0027t he?","answer":"Well, he\u0027s certainly playing a power game, but he\u0027s playing it with people like Warner Brothers, CBS, Les Moonves, Chuck Laurie.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":54,"aSentId":55},{"question":"You wouldn\u0027t deny taking hits of cocaine?","answer":"Well, no, of course not.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":68,"aSentId":69},{"question":"What did you make of the whole interview in context?","answer":"I just felt -- I felt a heavy heart.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":92,"aSentId":93},{"question":"And if that private life is not adversely affecting his professional working environment, and it didn\u0027t seem to be much, then what\u0027s the problem?","answer":"Well, I think there is a problem because, number one, as Bob said earlier, it was spiraling out of control.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":127,"aSentId":128},{"question":"I mean, do you look at a guy and think his life\u0027s in danger?","answer":"You know, I try to -- I tend to just focus on the here and now.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":143,"aSentId":144},{"question":"Does he take any personal responsibility for the deaths of his people right now?","answer":"When we ask about that, though, he says no, no reasonable person would shoot peaceful protesters.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":206,"aSentId":207},{"question":"Does he think he can just ride this out?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":211,"aSentId":212},{"question":"And if that is the case, is this good for America and the west, do you think?","answer":"Well, to your question about whether it\u0027s anti- American or whether it\u0027s the people here themselves, it is the people in this region themselves.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":222,"aSentId":223},{"question":"Harvey, how are you?","answer":"Piers, I\u0027m -- couldn\u0027t be better.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":240,"aSentId":241},{"question":"Does it get better in Hollywood than being the guy that produced \"the movie\"?","answer":"Well, I was executive producer, but I had a bit to do with it.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":242,"aSentId":243},{"question":"What happens in there?","answer":"No kneecap.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":274,"aSentId":275},{"question":"What\u0027s the business of turning around an Oscar campaign?","answer":"First of all, \"Social Network\" is a fabulous movie.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":278,"aSentId":279},{"question":"But how did you kill it?","answer":"I have to win for me, and I didn\u0027t kill them.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":282,"aSentId":283},{"question":"What was the key thing that you felt you had to do to get this film back on its tracks?","answer":"I think losing the Golden Globe for best picture for me, feeling that that was something that we could win was the absolute thing that instead of making me quit like a lot of people said, absolutely motivated me the complete opposite way.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":300,"aSentId":301},{"question":"What are the key things you had to change?","answer":"There\u0027s only one thing to really do.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":304,"aSentId":305},{"question":"How important is it to get your front people out there selling that movie?","answer":"It\u0027s important to get it -- a movie connected to an audience, and it\u0027s important in an Oscar campaign.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":315,"aSentId":316},{"question":"ORGAN: When you heard the words \"best movie , \u0027The King\u0027s Speech\u0027,\" what did you feel?","answer":"I was elated.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":324,"aSentId":325},{"question":"One of the greatest moments of your life?","answer":"It\u0027s fantastic.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":328,"aSentId":329},{"question":"What did you make -- what do you make of the Charlie Sheen story from a position of being a top producer in Hollywood?","answer":"I worked with Charlie Sheen.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":344,"aSentId":345},{"question":"ORGAN: You think so?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":357,"aSentId":358},{"question":"Would you hire Charlie Sheen?","answer":"I\u0027d hire Charlie Sheen to do \"Scary Movie 4, 5, 6, 7.\"","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":378,"aSentId":379},{"question":"Would you put him in a series maybe or no?","answer":"I don\u0027t make TV series, so thank god.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":381,"aSentId":382},{"question":"How many Oscars have you got at home?","answer":"I have about -- probably 15 or 20 at home.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":400,"aSentId":401},{"question":"OK?","answer":"You\u0027ve got your work cut out there.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":419,"aSentId":420},{"question":"If you could make the ultimate movie for people dead or alive, you know, director, producer, leading man, leading lady, who would it be?","answer":"Well, I own a book called \"Mila 18\".","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":429,"aSentId":430},{"question":"And who would produce it?","answer":"Probably producing it would be Hal Wallace and there\u0027s actually somebody alive who is young -- a young man at 87 years old, his name is Walter Mirsh.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":438,"aSentId":439},{"question":"Best actor and actress you\u0027ve ever seen?","answer":"I think Katherine Hepburn could play the leading lady.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":445,"aSentId":446},{"question":"And the man?","answer":"Both Hepburns could play that.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":448,"aSentId":449},{"question":"What\u0027s the simple answer?","answer":"The simple answer is if you don\u0027t tell the story from both sides, you will never understand everything we\u0027re watching in Libya, Egypt, you know, et cetera.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":492,"aSentId":493},{"question":"Was that your intention, was it designed to inspire people more than anything else?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":523,"aSentId":524},{"question":"And she got -- she married four times and I think you moved how -- 17 times in 12 years?","answer":"By the time I was 18, yes.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":531,"aSentId":532},{"question":"But the sexual abuse?","answer":"The sexual abuse, listen, when you\u0027re -- when you\u0027re 10 years old and you try to tell your parents, first of all the -- the -- the perpetrator says, you know, no one will believe you.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":539,"aSentId":540},{"question":"So what does she make of it?","answer":"She said it\u0027s pretty personal.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":549,"aSentId":550},{"question":"But did -- did part of you think I should talk about this before other people do as your star rises?","answer":"No, it wasn\u0027t that.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":581,"aSentId":582},{"question":"Was that at the back of our mind as well?","answer":"Not -- not -- not with the abuse stuff.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":583,"aSentId":584},{"question":"I mean, were you aware that what he was doing was wrong?","answer":"ROWN: Oh, absolutely.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":604,"aSentId":605},{"question":"Why was that?","answer":"Embarrassment.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":622,"aSentId":623},{"question":"Well what are your thoughts to the man that abused you?","answer":"Well, I\u0027ve moved on.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":656,"aSentId":657},{"question":"Strange feeling, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Yes, a little bit yes.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":666,"aSentId":667},{"question":"And how bad was that?","answer":"It was -- well, obviously you read the book --","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":679,"aSentId":680},{"question":"He punching you?","answer":"Yes, yes, we\u0027d be kind of banging on each other.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":695,"aSentId":696},{"question":"And the judge, I think, is very smart, isn\u0027t he?","answer":"Brilliant.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":703,"aSentId":704},{"question":"Tell me again what he does?","answer":"Well, it was Judge Zolf (ph) from Salem.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":705,"aSentId":706},{"question":"Do you think he regrets what he did?","answer":"He -- we were out about three weeks ago, went to breakfast and he said -- he looked me right in the eye and he said you know, I just want to say I\u0027m sorry.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":748,"aSentId":749},{"question":"But I can see in you now that that makes you emotional, doesn\u0027t it?","answer":"Yes, Yes.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":761,"aSentId":762},{"question":"Is he proud of you now, do you think?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":768,"aSentId":769},{"question":"Was your mom there as well?","answer":"Yes, mom\u0027s right next to Aryana (ph) absolutely.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":788,"aSentId":789},{"question":"Does it have your head on it?","answer":"I wish it did.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":802,"aSentId":803},{"question":"It\u0027s been a very emotional 20 minutes, hasn\u0027t it?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":808,"aSentId":809},{"question":"What does that mean?","answer":"It meant nothing.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":827,"aSentId":828},{"question":"For what?","answer":"You know what I\u0027m asking you.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":845,"aSentId":846},{"question":"Could you be tempted to run for president?","answer":"No.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":853,"aSentId":854},{"question":"What do -- what do you make of what\u0027s happening in the Middle East in the context of America?","answer":"Well, I\u0027m hopeful because people are obviously seeking freedom and democracy.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":861,"aSentId":862},{"question":"When you see what\u0027s going on in the Middle East, where it\u0027s happening in an evolutionary way, through the grass roots or the people themselves, isn\u0027t it a better way for America to go in the future?","answer":"Well, I think every -- every situation, you have to take it on its own merits.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":865,"aSentId":866},{"question":"That\u0027s it?","answer":"That\u0027s it.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":888,"aSentId":889},{"question":"How about that?","answer":"OK, whatever.","docId":"110301pmt","qSentId":891,"aSentId":892}]